<subSubSection id="C3025DA0FFF0FC4EFF6952B28A5EF1FC" box="[168,530,1433,1457]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="8BA70E2BFFF0FC4EFF6952B28A5EF1FC" blockId="0.[168,775,1433,1877]" box="[168,530,1433,1457]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">The Mouse-colored Tyrannulet,</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3025DA0FFF0FC4EFDE452B2897AF199" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BA70E2BFFF0FC4EFDE452B2897AF199" blockId="0.[168,775,1433,1877]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicName id="4C1875A8FFF0FC4EFDE452B2897EF199" authority="(Spix, 1825)" authorityName="Spix" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1825" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Phaeomyias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="murina">
<emphasis id="B96CD239FFF0FC4EFDE452B28B4BF1FD" box="[549,775,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Phaeomyias murina</emphasis>
(Spix, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
,
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3025DA0FFF0FC4EFE8152978967F3E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA70E2BFFF0FC4EFE8152978A5AF318" blockId="0.[168,775,1433,1877]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
has a wide distribution in the Neotropics, ranging from 
<collectingCountry id="F30F4EBBFFF0FC4EFEFC52F489FEF1BA" box="[317,434,1503,1527]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry id="F30F4EBBFFF0FC4EFDF652F48AEDF1BA" box="[567,673,1503,1527]" name="Argentina" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4EFD7052F48914F257" author="Ridgely RS &amp; Tudor G" bookContentInfo="750 p." journalOrPublisher="University of Texas Press, Austin" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" refString="Ridgely RS, Tudor G (2009) Field Guide to the Songbirds of South America: The Passerines. University of Texas Press, Austin, 750 p." title="Field Guide to the Songbirds of South America: The Passerines" type="book" year="2009">Ridgely and Tudor 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4EFEA451298AE8F257" author="Fitzpatrick J &amp; Kirwan GM" box="[357,676,1538,1562]" editor="del Hoyo J" journalOrPublisher="Lynx Edicions, Barcelona" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" publicationUrl="http://www.hbw.com/node/57185" refString="Fitzpatrick J Kirwan GM (2017) Mouse-colored Tyrannulet (Phaeomyias murina). In: del Hoyo J, Elliott A, Christie DA, Juana E (Eds) Handbook of the Birds of the World Alive. Lynx Edicions, Barce- lona. http: // www. hbw. com / node / 57185. Acessed on: 2017 - 5 - 2." title="Mouse-colored Tyrannulet (Phaeomyias murina)" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Handbook of the Birds of the World Alive. Lynx Edicions, Barce- lona" year="2017">Fitzpatrick and Kirwan 2017</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F30F4EBBFFF0FC4EFD1651298889F270" name="Brazil" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, its occurs in the southernmost part of the country in all states except 
<collectingRegion id="49DCC0C9FFF0FC4EFE9E516389B2F22D" box="[351,510,1608,1632]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49DCC0C9FFF0FC4EFDF951638B4BF22D" box="[568,775,1608,1632]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
Rio 
<collectingRegion id="49DCC0C9FFF0FC4EFDA651638B4BF22D" box="[615,775,1608,1632]" inferredBySuffix="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4EFF705140896DF2CE" author="Sick H" bookContentInfo="912 pp." box="[177,289,1643,1667]" journalOrPublisher="Nova Fronteira, Rio de Janeiro" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" refString="Sick H (1997) Ornitologia Brasileira. Nova Fronteira, Rio de Janeiro, 912 pp." title="Ornitologia Brasileira" type="book" year="1997">Sick 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4EFEEF514089FDF2CE" author="Sigrist T" bookContentInfo="600 pp." box="[302,433,1643,1667]" journalOrPublisher="Avis Brasilis, Sao Paulo" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" refString="Sigrist T (2009) Guia de Campo Avis Brasilis-Avifauna Brasileira: descricao das especies. 1 ª ed. Avis Brasilis, Sao Paulo, 600 pp." title="Guia de Campo Avis Brasilis-Avifauna Brasileira: descricao das especies. 1 ª ed" type="book" year="2009">Sigrist 2009</bibRefCitation>
). This species occupies a great variety of forest habitats, in addition to parks, gardens, mangroves, shrubby areas and the cerrado (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4EFD50519A88AEF2A1" author="Fitzpatrick JW" editor="del Hoyo J" journalOrPublisher="Lynx Edicions, Barcelona" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" pagination="170 - 462" refString="Fitzpatrick JW (2004) Family Tyrannidae (tyrant-flycatchers). In: del Hoyo J, Elliott A, Christie DA (Eds) Handbook of the Birds of the World. Volume 9. Lynx Edicions, Barcelona, 170 - 462." title="Family Tyrannidae (tyrant-flycatchers)" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Handbook of the Birds of the World. Volume 9" year="2004">Fitzpatrick 2004</bibRefCitation>
). However, it prefers semi-open environments, either xerophilous or subxerophilous (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4EFDFA51DC88ADF37F" author="Giraudo AR &amp; Baldo JL" journalOrPublisher="Hornero" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" pagination="1 - 9" part="15" refString="Giraudo AR, Baldo JL (1998) Distribucion y biologia de Phaeomyias murina (Tyrannidae) en el Nordeste de Argentina. Hornero 15 (1): 1 - 9." title="Distribucion y biologia de Phaeomyias murina (Tyrannidae) en el Nordeste de Argentina" type="journal article" year="1998">Giraudo and Baldo 1998</bibRefCitation>
), occupying the middle and lower strata of vegetation (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4EFF2050168A47F318" author="Narosky T &amp; Yzurieta D" bookContentInfo="432 pp." box="[225,523,1853,1877]" journalOrPublisher="Vazquez Mazzini Editores, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" refString="Narosky T, Yzurieta D (2010) Aves de Argentina y Uruguay: Guia de Identificacion. 16 ª ed. Vazquez Mazzini Editores, Buenos Aires, 432 pp." title="Aves de Argentina y Uruguay: Guia de Identificacion. 16 ª ed" type="book" year="2010">Narosky and Yzurieta 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA70E2BFFF0FC4EFF6950A28967F3E6" blockId="0.[168,299,1929,1963]" box="[168,299,1929,1963]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
<heading id="D0EFB947FFF0FC4EFF6950A28967F3E6" box="[168,299,1929,1963]" fontSize="14" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" reason="1">Methods</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3025DA0FFF0FC4EFF6950E88C83F35F" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BA70E2BFFF0FC4EFF6950E88C83F35F" blockId="0.[168,775,1987,2011]" lastBlockId="0.[813,1420,1374,1810]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
<materialsCitation id="3B700476FFF0FC4EFF6950E88D49F1F6" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1656656759" collectingDate="2013-12-12" collectorName="On &amp; de Novembro" country="Brazil" county="Rio Ijui" elevation="3" latitude="-28.179443" location="Dezesseis de Novembro" longLatPrecision="20" longitude="-55.053333" municipality="The" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Rio Grande do Sul">
<collectorName id="26ED6BFDFFF0FC4EFF6950E88885F396" box="[168,201,1987,2011]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">On</collectorName>
<collectingDate id="EFE2D103FFF0FC4EFF0C50E889DBF396" box="[205,407,1987,2011]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" value="2013-12-12">
<date id="FFA628EBFFF0FC4EFF0C50E889DBF396" box="[205,407,1987,2011]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" value="2013-12-12">12 December 2013</date>
</collectingDate>
, I found 1 individual in vocal activity in a gallery forest in the municipality of 
<location id="8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFAC352758BD3F1D4" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B1BF3DFFF0FC4CFF6952B28D61F5E1:8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFAC352758BD3F1D4" country="Brazil" county="Rio Ijui" latitude="-28.179443" longLatPrecision="20" longitude="-55.053333" municipality="The" name="Dezesseis de Novembro" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" stateProvince="Rio Grande do Sul">
Dezesseis 
<collectorName id="26ED6BFDFFF0FC4EFAB352758BD3F1D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">de Novembro</collectorName>
</location>
(
<geoCoordinate id="EE2C68ECFFF0FC4EFC7052548C75F1D4" box="[945,1081,1407,1433]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" precision="15" value="-28.179443">28°10′46″ S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE2C68ECFFF0FC4EFB8852548CA6F1D4" box="[1097,1258,1407,1433]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" precision="15" value="-55.053333">055°03′12″ W</geoCoordinate>
), northwestern 
<collectingRegion id="49DCC0C9FFF0FC4EFCEC52888BB4F1F6" box="[813,1016,1443,1467]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
Rio 
<collectingRegion id="49DCC0C9FFF0FC4EFC9B52888BB4F1F6" box="[858,1016,1443,1467]" inferredBySuffix="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F30F4EBBFFF0FC4EFBA752888CEBF1F6" box="[1126,1191,1443,1467]" name="Brazil" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="132312AEFFF0FC4EFB7752888CB9F1F6" box="[1206,1269,1443,1467]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[168,230,1600,1620]" captionTargetBox="[261,1327,181,1554]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[244,1344,160,1574]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Global distribution of the Mouse-colored Tyrannulet, Phaeomyias murina (in gray) (sensu BirdLife International 2014) and the new record in Dezesseis de Novembro municipality (red dot), state of Rio Grande do Sul, southern Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/998845/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
<location id="8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFACD52888D0CF1F6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B1BF3DFFF0FC4CFF6952B28D61F5E1:8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFACD52888D0CF1F6" box="[1292,1344,1443,1467]" country="Brazil" county="Rio Ijui" latitude="-28.179443" longLatPrecision="20" longitude="-55.053333" municipality="The" name="Both" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" stateProvince="Rio Grande do Sul">Both</location>
a photograph (
<figureCitation id="132312AEFFF0FC4EFC4F52EE8B83F190" box="[910,975,1477,1501]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="2.[168,230,769,789]" captionTargetBox="[165,777,157,747]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[165,777,157,747]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 2. Individual of the Mouse-colored Tyrannulet, Phaeomyias murina, photographed on 12 December 2013 in the municipality of Dezesseis de Novembro, northwestern Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil. Photograph by M. S. Pereira." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/998847/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and an audio recording (after playback) were obtained as evidence for the record. Additional photographs were published on the 
<location id="8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFB0851218D61F26F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B1BF3DFFF0FC4CFF6952B28D61F5E1:8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFB0851218D61F26F" box="[1225,1325,1546,1570]" country="Brazil" county="Rio Ijui" latitude="-28.179443" longLatPrecision="20" longitude="-55.053333" municipality="The" name="Wikiaves" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" stateProvince="Rio Grande do Sul">Wikiaves</location>
website (http://www.wikiaves.com) and the voice recording was uploaded in the online digital archive 
<location id="8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFB7A51658D71F22B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B1BF3DFFF0FC4CFF6952B28D61F5E1:8EC758F0FFF0FC4EFB7A51658D71F22B" box="[1211,1341,1614,1638]" country="Brazil" county="Rio Ijui" latitude="-28.179443" longLatPrecision="20" longitude="-55.053333" municipality="The" name="Xeno-Canto" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" stateProvince="Rio Grande do Sul">Xeno-Canto</location>
(http:// www.xeno-canto.org) under the number 
<accessionNumber id="944B93C8FFF0FC4EFB21515B8D14F2C5" box="[1248,1368,1648,1672]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/XC367617" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">XC367617</accessionNumber>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC39451FFF0FC4EFAA3515A8DC7F2C4" box="[1378,1419,1649,1673]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">The</collectingMunicipality>
locality is near the 
<collectingCounty id="62C676A7FFF0FC4EFBC551B88C15F2E6" box="[1028,1113,1683,1707]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Rio Ijuí</collectingCounty>
and is characterized by the presence of small xerophytic woodlands with approximately 
<elevation id="0035E918FFF0FC4EFCBE51FC8BE7F2A2" box="[895,939,1751,1775]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" unit="m" value="3.0">
<quantity id="4CE0A3CEFFF0FC4EFCBE51FC8BE7F2A2" box="[895,939,1751,1775]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
</elevation>
high, interspersed with grasslands used for cattle ranching and agriculture (
<figureCitation id="132312AEFFF0FC4EFB4151D18C8DF35F" box="[1152,1217,1786,1810]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="2.[168,230,2014,2034]" captionTargetBox="[168,776,1533,1989]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[168,776,1533,1989]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 3. Habitat occupied by the Mouse-colored Tyrannulet, Phaeomyias murina, at Dezesseis de Novembro, northwestern Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil. Photograph by M. S. Pereira." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/998849/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3025DA0FFF0FC4CFCEC506E8D61F5E1" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA70E2BFFF0FC4EFCEC506E8BD7F32A" blockId="0.[813,923,1861,1895]" box="[813,923,1861,1895]" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
<heading id="D0EFB947FFF0FC4EFCEC506E8BD7F32A" box="[813,923,1861,1895]" fontSize="14" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" reason="1">Results</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA70E2BFFF0FC4FFCEC50548B9EF36D" blockId="0.[813,1419,1918,2011]" lastBlockId="1.[813,1420,1699,2096]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="0" pageNumber="525">
To confirm the identity of the bird, I compared the photographs obtained in the field with illustrations and descriptions presented in the literature (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF0FC4FFACB50E88966F2F6" author="Ridgely RS &amp; Tudor G" bookContentInfo="750 p." journalOrPublisher="University of Texas Press, Austin" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="0" pageNumber="525" refString="Ridgely RS, Tudor G (2009) Field Guide to the Songbirds of South America: The Passerines. University of Texas Press, Austin, 750 p." title="Field Guide to the Songbirds of South America: The Passerines" type="book" year="2009">Ridgely and Tudor 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF1FC4FFEFB5188898DF2F6" author="Sigrist T" bookContentInfo="600 pp." box="[314,449,1699,1723]" journalOrPublisher="Avis Brasilis, Sao Paulo" pageId="1" pageNumber="526" refString="Sigrist T (2009) Guia de Campo Avis Brasilis-Avifauna Brasileira: descricao das especies. 1 ª ed. Avis Brasilis, Sao Paulo, 600 pp." title="Guia de Campo Avis Brasilis-Avifauna Brasileira: descricao das especies. 1 ª ed" type="book" year="2009">Sigrist 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8973DAFFF1FC4FFE1151888B4FF2F6" author="Narosky T &amp; Yzurieta D" bookContentInfo="432 pp." box="[464,771,1699,1723]" journalOrPublisher="Vazquez Mazzini Editores, Buenos Aires" pageId="1" pageNumber="526" refString="Narosky T, Yzurieta D (2010) Aves de Argentina y Uruguay: Guia de Identificacion. 16 ª ed. Vazquez Mazzini Editores, Buenos Aires, 432 pp." title="Aves de Argentina y Uruguay: Guia de Identificacion. 16 ª ed" type="book" year="2010">Narosky and Yzurieta 2010</bibRefCitation>
, Fitzpatrick and Kirwan 201 7). The overall brownish coloration of the upperparts, rather broad whitish supercilium and conspicuous dirty white wing-bars, along with bill shape and color (dusky with mandible pale-colored at base), are distinguishing field marks that in combination allow to exclude potential confusion species present in the same area, such as the Southern Beardless-Tyrannulet, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1875A8FFF1FC4FFF6950998AD7F387" authority="(Temminck, 1824)" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1824" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[168,667,1969,1994]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Camptostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obsoletum">
<emphasis id="B96CD239FFF1FC4FFF69509989F5F384" box="[168,441,1969,1993]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="526">Camptostoma obsoletum</emphasis>
(Temminck, 1824)
</taxonomicName>
and the Southern Scrub-Flycatcher, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1875A8FFF1FC4FFE1750F888A4FC40" authority="(Wied, 1831)" authorityName="Wied" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="Wied" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Sublegatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="modestus">
<emphasis id="B96CD239FFF1FC4FFE1750F88AF9F3A6" box="[470,693,2003,2027]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="526">Sublegatus modestus</emphasis>
(Wied, 1831)
</taxonomicName>
. I also compared the audio recording with vocal samples deposited at the Xeno-Canto and found that it presents the same structure of several recordings from southeastern and southwestern Brazil (e.g., XC20300 and XC10219 from São Paulo, and XC81646 from Mato Grosso do Sul).
</paragraph>
